    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Right, exactly. It feels like people struggle to see that even \"protecting\" users is just a way to control what they see. Do you think most people just fail to understand this because they prioritize safety over actual liberty, or is there a fundamental flaw in the way current democratic legal frameworks view the internet?",
